The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block lets you to fine tune your rifle's gas system for smoother cycling and operation. Regulating the amount of gas used to cycle the action allows tuning the rifle’s operation to a specific load and the use of low mass bolt carriers, buffers and springs to reduce felt recoil. This is critical to allow faster follow up shots, target acquisition and reliability.
The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block is field adjustable. Operation is easy, simply turn the gas regulating screw in to lessen the amount of gas and out to add more gas, then use the brass set screw to lock the setting in place. The overall height of the gas block is 1.37” with left to right dimensions at .94” to fit under most hand guards and still have the customization of an adjustable gas block.
Melonite Coated to reduce wear and corrosion for extended periods of fire, it also makes cleaning easier, as carbon build up will not adhere to the non-reflective coated surface as much as it does on standard Parkerized finishes.

Markings: The right side of the barrel is marked “Smith & Wesson”. The right sideplate is marked “S&W 500” and the right side of the frame has the Marcas Registradas address. The left side of the barrel reads “500 S&W MAGNUM” The left side of the frame is marked with the S&W logo and an “L” with a counter clockwise arrow. The yoke cut is marked “CHR3248 / MOD 500” and the yoke is marked “159”. The butt is marked “CHR3248”.

Barrel Length: The barrel measures 9” to the end of the compensator

Sights / Optics: The front sight is a Patridge style blade on an elevated ribbed base. The rear sight is an S&W Micrometer Click square notch adjustable for windage and elevation.

Stock Configuration & Condition: The one piece round butt Hogue Monogrips are textured rubber with finger grooves and imprinted S&W logos. There is little to no wear. The grips rate in about Excellent overall condition.

Type of Finish: Stainless Steel

Finish Originality: All Original

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling is sharp. There is no erosion in the bore, but there is a bit of fouling which needs to be cleaned.

Overall Condition: This handgun retains about 95% of its metal finish. There is some dried red grease which is difficult to remove. Once removed, there are some tarnished spots that are left behind mostly on the rear face of the cylinder. As this is a stainless gun, we believe it may clean up with considerable time and effort. This substance is found on the underside of the hammer, top strap, cylinder, in the bolt stop cuts, and around the cylinder release. The screw heads are Sharp. The markings are Clear. Overall, this handgun rates in about Fine condition.

Mechanics: The action functions correctly in both single and double action. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: This revolver comes in a blue plastic S&W carry case. The end label does not correctly describe the pistol. The case shows only light storage wear and is in Excellent condition.

Our Assessment: The Smith & Wesson site has this to say about the massive 500 Magnum revolver: “In 2003 the gunsmiths and engineers at Smith & Wesson wanted to deliver maximum power for serious handgun hunters. The power they sought required an entirely new frame, the massive "X-Frame," and was the basis for the new Model S&W 500, the most powerful production revolver in the world. This ushered in the era of the "big gun" and was only the beginning. For ultimate power and velocity there's nothing even close to an X-Frame model handgun.” This is the ultimate in deep woods defense and handgun hunting. Strap this beast to a shoulder holster and be ready for anything. With some diligent cleaning and scrubbing, this will be a stainless beauty once again.
